column5: Hello all, we are thinking of getting away for a long weekend. Any advice on resorts north of Barrie? Something nice but not going to breaking my pocket book!  Afterall we were just married  lol.  Any advice would help us out.  John

Lots of good people here to help you out.  I'll bet the time of year that you are looking at as well as a rough idea of the area you are looking at will help get the ball rolling.  North of Barrie is pretty vast.  Cheers  Craig

How far North of Barrie do you want to go? Are you looking for somewhere you can do some ice fishing? There are plenty of resorts in the Muskoka area, if you pick an area you are interesteded in and just type in "resorts (and whatever area you want) in Goggle, you will get plenty of listings and information on them.  Enjoy your weekend away!
Two items in the Auction for Tyler section !  As mentioned... what do you want to do? How far are you willing to drive? What do you expect included? Budget?
I wouldnt want to go any further than Muskoka area.Budget is tight! Ice fishing a must.  Thanks John
if you find this place let me know, I always thought it didn't exist
true enough,I guess its wishful thinkin on my part lol.
